	<Language_en_US>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_UNIT_EXOTIC_UNIT_FLYING_CIRCUS">
			<Text>[ICON_IDEOLOGY_AUTOCRACY] Flying Circus</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_UNIT_EXOTIC_UNIT_FLYING_CIRCUS_HELP">
			<Text>Early air unit designed to intercept incoming enemy aircraft. Price shown is how much it costs to hire this unit for 20 turns.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_UNIT_EXOTIC_UNIT_FLYING_CIRCUS_STRATEGY">
			<Text>The Flying Circus is an early air unit. It can be based in any city you own or aboard an aircraft carrier. It can move from city to city, or carrier, and can perform 'missions' within its range of 5 tiles. Use the Flying Circus to attack enemy aircraft and ground units, to scout enemy positions, and to defend against enemy air attacks. See the rules on Aircraft for more information.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_UNIT_EXOTIC_UNIT_FLYING_CIRCUS_PEDIA">
			<Text>
				The Flying Circus is a Modern Era Fighter unit, available when the civilization discovers Steam Power. The Mercenary Consulate is required for this unit to be built. The Flying Circus becomes obsolete upon the discovery of Lasers.[NEWLINE][NEWLINE]
				Jagdgeschwader 1, or JG 1, of World War I, was a fighter wing of the German Luftstreitkraefte, comprising four Jastas, or fighter squadrons. The first unit of its type formed under that classification, JG I was formed on 24 June 1917, with Manfred von Richthofen as commanding officer, by combining Jastas 4, 6, 10 and 11. JG 1 became known as 'The Flying Circus' or 'Richthofen's Circus' because of the bright colours of its aircraft, and perhaps also because of the way the unit was transferred from one area of Allied air activity to another, moving like a travelling circus in trains, and frequently setting up in tents on improvised airfields.
			</Text>
		</Row>
	</Language_en_US>
  
